---
const features = [
  {
    title: "Find what AST-pattern matchers miss.",
    description:
      "The inter-procedural dataflow engine tracks untrusted data across function boundaries, persistence layers, aliases, and async code. 100+ rules across 20+ vulnerability classes.",
  },
  {
    title: "One finding becomes total coverage.",
    description:
      "AST-pattern rules let you enact a rule from every vulnerability you uncover, and the engine applies it across the entire codebase, deterministically, in minutes of CPU.",
  },
  {
    title: "Open source, batteries included.",
    description:
      "Engine, rules, CI integrations — the entire stack ships under Apache 2.0 and MIT. No paid tier to unlock taint tracking, no gates on writing your own rules.",
  },
];
---

<section class="band band-tint" aria-labelledby="what-heading">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <h2 id="what-heading" class="section-title text-center">What is OpenTaint?</h2>
    <p class="subheadline">
      Formal taint analysis for application security — finds what AST-pattern matchers miss, lets LLM agents enact rules from vulnerabilities, scales where neither can alone.
    </p>

    <h2 id="why-heading" class="section-title mt-12 lg:mt-14 text-center">Why is OpenTaint?</h2>
    <p class="subheadline">
      AI generates production code faster than today's security tooling can keep up with.
    </p>
    <p class="subheadline">
      LLM security agents find vulnerabilities humans miss, burn tokens on every file, and still can't guarantee they catch everything.
    </p>
    <p class="subheadline">
      The more AI writes code, the more you need formal methods underneath.
    </p>

    <ul class="mt-8 space-y-4 text-left lg:mt-10 lg:space-y-5">
      {features.map((feature) => (
        <li class="flex gap-3 font-mono text-[15px] leading-[185%] lg:text-base lg:gap-4">
          <span class="mt-[0.65em] h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <div>
            <strong class="feature-title">{feature.title}</strong>
            <span class="text-muted-foreground">{feature.description}</span>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </div>

</section>
